<br />
<br />current version is v0.02
<br />
<br />which all i did was undo the crap from v0.01 and redo what i did in v0.00 in order to make syntax and opcode definitions load *properly*
<br />
<br />i will get working again on the "assembly-ing" portion maybe this weekend or next week.
<br />v0.02 comes with win32 binary already compiled.
<br />
<br />all v0.02 does is show status of progression in loading the syntax file.
<br />
<br />if you have WINE you can prolly get it to run under Linux.
<br />
<br />my long term goal is to transcode the Blitz BASIC 3D 1.99 source code over to C that way i can recompile it using GCC, then use that CHASM as the assembler module for GCC in order to re-assemble itself for other systems.

		

